===noun===

etymology: from the United States Army [[acronym]] "Absent Without Leave"

# the status of being absent from the command and control of a military organization without being placed on leave, detached to another unit, or otherwise receiving official sanction for an absence
# a person who holds AWOL status

===Usage===

The United States [[Marine]] Corps uses the term "UA" (''Unauthorized Absence'') instead of "AWOL".